Parents were calling for the expulsion of a Grade 9 pupil, who allegedly assaulted a fellow pupil in a gruesome attack at Fourways High School in Johannesburg. A case of assault with intent to cause grievous bodily harm was opened at the Douglasdale police station shortly after the incident and the victim, 15, was hospitalised after allegedly being beaten unconscious. According to sources close to the victim, his injuries were so severe he underwent multiple surgeries, brain scans and tests before he could finally return to school last week. The incident happened on 30 January. Police spokesperson Kay Makhubela confirmed...